# Endpoints

---

## POST /payments

### Description

Create a new payment request.

### Request Body

* amount (decimal, required)
* currency (string, required)
* payerId (UUID, required)
* payeeId (UUID, required)
* idempotencyKey (string, required)

### Responses

* 201 Created → Payment created successfully
* 200 OK → Existing payment returned (idempotency hit)
* 400 Bad Request → Validation error
* 409 Conflict → Duplicate inconsistent request

---

## GET /payments/{paymentId}

### Description

Retrieve payment details by ID.

### Responses

* 200 OK → Payment details returned
* 404 Not Found → Payment does not exist

---

## GET /payments/{paymentId}/status

### Description

Retrieve current status of a payment.

### Responses

* 200 OK → Payment status returned
* 404 Not Found → Payment does not exist

---

## POST /payments/{paymentId}/refunds

### Description

Initiate a refund for a completed payment.

### Request Body

* amount (decimal, optional for partial refund)
* reason (string, required)

### Responses

* 202 Accepted → Refund initiated
* 400 Bad Request → Invalid refund request
* 409 Conflict → Refund not allowed for payment state

---

## GET /payments/{paymentId}/refunds

### Description

Retrieve refund history for a payment.

### Responses

* 200 OK → List of refunds
* 404 Not Found → Payment does not exist

---

## POST /payments/reconcile

### Description

Trigger reconciliation process for external provider matching.

### Responses

* 202 Accepted → Reconciliation started
* 403 Forbidden → Unauthorized access

---

## GET /health

### Description

Service health check endpoint.

### Responses

* 200 OK → Service healthy
* 503 Service Unavailable → Service degraded

